snippet.textDisplay:
So many of Keith's issues are answered with two very simple things.
1. Whataburger doesn't have a great shelf life. If you don't eat it soon after it is made, you run into the issues described: some things are watery, some things dried out. The frys are a great example: fresh they are crispy, but 20 minutes later they are soggy.
2. ... They have salt. Just add salt. You'll add hot sauce to things, but not salt?
